{
  "texts": [
    "It remains to be seen if quantum computers could provide an unconditional superpolynomial advantage over classical computers in predicting ground state properties.",
    "We describe the key ideas behind the proof of Theorem 1.",
    "The proof is separated into three parts.",
    "The first part Supplementary Section 1 describes the existence of a simple functional form that approximates the ground state property TrðOρðxÞÞ.",
    "The second part in Supplementary Section 2 gives a new bound for the ℓ 1 -norm of the Pauli coefficients of the observable O when written in the Pauli basis."
  ]
}